00:07:49.830 --> 00:07:51.740
- One for Barbara Natterson.

00:07:51.740 --> 00:07:54.000
If chimpanzees are so
closely related to humans,

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:57.353
why do we use species like
mice that are so distant

00:07:57.353 --> 00:07:59.686
as models for human disease?

00:08:01.757 --> 00:08:03.246
- Well, there are a number of ways

00:08:03.246 --> 00:08:07.193
I could approach that question,
starting with the ethical

00:08:07.193 --> 00:08:08.865
or starting with the scientific.

00:08:08.865 --> 00:08:11.416
I guess my response quickly would be that

00:08:11.416 --> 00:08:15.125
we have been overall very
disappointed with the mouse model

00:08:15.125 --> 00:08:17.929
in many ways, you know it's
often said that we've cured

00:08:17.929 --> 00:08:21.483
cancer thousands of times
in mice, but the problem is

00:08:21.483 --> 00:08:23.614
it doesn't translate so well to humans.

00:08:23.614 --> 00:08:27.272
I guess my comment would
be that there are ways

00:08:27.272 --> 00:08:31.334
that we can begin to
advance science by looking

00:08:31.334 --> 00:08:34.778
at the natural occurrence of
disease in non-human animals

00:08:34.778 --> 00:08:37.654
because there are limitations
to experimental models.

00:08:37.654 --> 00:08:40.865
Don't get me wrong, experimental
models are very valuable

00:08:40.865 --> 00:08:43.874
and yet there's certain
diseases, for example bone cancer

00:08:43.874 --> 00:08:47.521
osteosarcoma which happens
very commonly in large dogs

00:08:47.521 --> 00:08:51.481
like Great Danes and
Labradors and Mastiffs

00:08:51.481 --> 00:08:54.762
and the biology, the natural
history of this kind of cancer

00:08:54.762 --> 00:08:58.929
in those dogs is nearly identical
to the biology in humans

00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:03.643
who develop this problem,
typically adolescents.

00:09:03.643 --> 00:09:07.259
And so this is an area that
we've really not looked at

00:09:07.259 --> 00:09:10.026
and is hiding in plain
sight, an opportunity

00:09:10.026 --> 00:09:13.445
to begin to understand and
ask important scientific

00:09:13.445 --> 00:09:18.236
questions by looking at
the animals all around us,

00:09:18.236 --> 00:09:22.190
not only our pets but also
wild animals, farm animals,

00:09:22.190 --> 00:09:26.355
who are one their own developing
many of the same diereses

00:09:26.355 --> 00:09:27.438
that we have.

