the last is Ruslan Medzhitov.

00:09:37.535 --> 00:09:42.003
Do you know, or would
you predict the effect

00:09:42.003 --> 00:09:45.384
of ketogenic metabolism on the outcome

00:09:45.384 --> 00:09:46.488
during a viral infection?

00:09:46.488 --> 00:09:51.480
And start by explaining what
ketogenic metabolism is.

00:09:51.480 --> 00:09:55.647
- So presumably, what was
meant as ketogenic diet,

00:09:58.860 --> 00:10:03.027
a diet that is rich in fats
and low in carbohydrates,

00:10:05.719 --> 00:10:07.961
similar to Atkins Diet for example.

00:10:07.961 --> 00:10:12.079
The answer is that it
depends on the duration

00:10:12.079 --> 00:10:15.658
of the ketogenic diet
and how extreme it is,

00:10:15.658 --> 00:10:19.825
if it's really only just fats
and no carbohydrates at all,

00:10:21.616 --> 00:10:26.193
and it depends on what
is the limiting factor

00:10:26.193 --> 00:10:29.958
during an infection, so we
shouldn't be just generalizing

00:10:29.958 --> 00:10:33.678
it into any viral infection,
even for a given viral

00:10:33.678 --> 00:10:38.032
infection, the limiting factor
could be viral-induced damage

00:10:38.032 --> 00:10:41.410
or it could be viral-induced inflammation,

00:10:41.410 --> 00:10:44.410
and ketogenic diet or ketons rather,

00:10:46.294 --> 00:10:49.544
have various anti-inflammatory effects.

00:10:52.052 --> 00:10:55.029
And that can help under
conditions when inflammation

00:10:55.029 --> 00:10:59.345
is the limiting factor,
but generally being

00:10:59.345 --> 00:11:02.678
on a ketogenic diet for long enough time

00:11:03.667 --> 00:11:06.997
and if it's a very
aggressive ketogenic diet,

00:11:06.997 --> 00:11:11.500
no carbohydrates at all, it
has also various side effects

00:11:11.500 --> 00:11:15.667
such as ketoacedosis, which
leads to a drop in the pH

00:11:17.889 --> 00:11:22.056
of the blood and that in
itself can have various effects

00:11:23.252 --> 00:11:27.920
that can be deleterious on
the outcome of the infection

00:11:27.920 --> 00:11:32.087
so there's a long way to say
that there is no simple recipe

00:11:34.597 --> 00:11:38.808
or when our study was
published, somebody asked me

00:11:38.808 --> 00:11:42.975
a question, how many candies
should I eat to prevent flu?

00:11:44.627 --> 00:11:47.960
There is no answer like that and I think

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:53.980
only one general implication
I would say is that

00:11:55.713 --> 00:11:59.546
it appears that our
bodies may have preference

00:12:00.799 --> 00:12:05.246
for what we want to eat and
what we want to avoid eating

00:12:05.246 --> 00:12:06.687
depending on our condition.

00:12:06.687 --> 00:12:10.319
We all experience that in
difference and it's most obvious

00:12:10.319 --> 00:12:14.139
in the case of an early pregnancy
when the food preferences

00:12:14.139 --> 00:12:17.632
change dramatically, but that
also seems to be the case

00:12:17.632 --> 00:12:22.623
with infections, so we have our
preferences for chicken soup

00:12:22.623 --> 00:12:26.527
versus honey and tea
versus other types of food

00:12:26.527 --> 00:12:30.463
and we think that these
are some ancient mechanisms

00:12:30.463 --> 00:12:33.667
telling us which type of
metabolism would be protective.

00:12:33.667 --> 00:12:36.561
But anything extreme, like ketogenic diet

00:12:36.561 --> 00:12:39.587
or any one of those
diets, it's all of course,

00:12:39.587 --> 00:12:42.688
much of it is nonsense
and we should just follow

00:12:42.688 --> 00:12:45.997
more natural desires, thank you.

00:12:45.997 --> 00:12:48.247
